Key Match Events: Antonín Barák received a red card early in the match.
Czech Republic scored their first goal at the 66th minute through Tomáš Souček.
Cenk Tosun scored the winning goal for Turkey in the 90th minute.
Post-Match Reflections: Turkey progressed to the last 16 despite being a man down.
Czech Republic were eliminated from the tournament.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was marked by high tension and physicality.
Heavy beer throwing by fans was noted during the game.
